item.title: Here's a thing or two to make you chuckle sensibly or quirk a smile
item.description: So this one is a special one in my Discord DM's. I love languages, I love puns, and I love self-made portmonteaus, but this was just a happy little accident I saw when visiting the library in Halmstad. Essentially, it's the embodiment of Swenglish. Us Swedes are decently good at English, but sometimes a bit of our native language intermingles with the foreign words inside our brains. The way I read it, the English translation says the door is a bit anxious, or perhaps frightened, rather than it is about to raise an alarm if trespassed upon. Or mayhap it is correct to say that a door is alarmed in that context? Either way, this phrasing amused me and I had to send it to my favourite New Yorker. And now, you've all seen it too! The door is alarmed

item.title: I have survived!! Something I thought I would not!!
item.description: Sepsis and a blood bacterial infection!!! My doctors and I thought I would die! Today I am thankful to reside on this planet!!!!!!! I made my peace with death but truly I am so thankful to have more time on the planet to love and live and paint and sing and dance!!!! I want my US government to change and my life to improve!! I have never felt so grateful for my life and goddamn for modern medicine!!!! P.s. if I didn't have the right to an abortion that may have killed me!! Waiting to get care or to receive treatment! I love my Michigan Governor who protects my rights and feeds kids!!!
